            <thetext>The qx.ui.table.selection.Model.iterateSelection() method does not give the possibility to stop looping through all the elements of the selection once the user-provided iterator function has detected that it does not need to continue.

This would be a welcome optimization, since the only other way to iterate trough the selection is to use the getSelectedRanges() method which is not so straightforward.

An easy solution would be to check for a strict return value of false and break from the loop if that is the case.</thetext>
